						<summary>

						<p>Records the creation of an endowment of sixty <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by Sōmadēvabhaṭṭaṉ of Pāppaṉachchēri in Tirukkaṇṇamaṅgalam in Tirumarugal-nāḍu for feeding a brāhmaṇa well-versed in the <hi rend="italic">vēdas.</hi></p>						

						<p>The epigraph is in two sections, one in Sanskrit engraved in Grantha and the other in Tamil characters of about the 10th century. The record which is dated in the 4th year in the reign of a Rājakēsarivarmaṉ may be assigned to Gaṇḍarāditya or Sundara-chōḷa on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
